N ( here 3 ) Consecutive Numbers

--------------------------------------------------------

USING CTE and SELF JOIN 

WITH Three_count_Num AS (
SELECT NUM 
FROM LOGS 
GROUP BY 
HAVING COUNT(*)>=3
)

SELECT DISTINCT NUM 
FROM LOGS L1 
INNER JOIN Three_count_Num TCN 
ON TCN.NUM = L1.NUM 
INNER JOIN LOGS L2 
ON L2.NUM = TCN.NUM 
AND L1.ID+1 = L2.ID 
INNER JOIN LOGS L3 
ON L3.NUM = TCN.NUM 
AND L1.ID+2 = L3.ID 


1. Performance - Here, I have introduced a pre-aggregation step, assuming that this would reduce the candidate values
But if many survive the filter, then the aggregation cost outweighs the savings. With Window functions, LAG is preferred, which saves multiple self-joins.
